#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/mia/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/js-combine-iterations.md
M|rules|title: Combine Multiple Array Iterations
M|rules|impact: LOW-MEDIUM
M|rules|impactDescription: reduces iterations
M|rules|tags: javascript, arrays, loops, performance
M|rules|Multiple `.filter()` or `.map()` calls iterate the array multiple times. Combine into one loop.
M|rules|**Incorrect (3 iterations):**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|const admins = users.filter(u => u.isAdmin)
M|rules|const testers = users.filter(u => u.isTester)
M|rules|const inactive = users.filter(u => !u.isActive)
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (1 iteration):**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|const admins: User[] = []
M|rules|const testers: User[] = []
M|rules|const inactive: User[] = []
M|rules|for (const user of users) {
M|rules|if (user.isAdmin) admins.push(user)
M|rules|if (user.isTester) testers.push(user)
M|rules|if (!user.isActive) inactive.push(user)
M|rules|}
M|rules|```